I'm using es5-shim, es6-shim, and lodash 4.13.1, and the following outputs true instead of false in PhantomJS 2.1.1:

```
var initialSet = new Set();
var newSet = new Set(["test"]);
console.log(_.isEqual(initialSet, newSet));
```

After some digging, it looks like the problem is that `_.isEqual` uses the object tag. In Chrome, for instance, the tag for the set is [object Set], but in PhantomJS the tag is [object Object], so `_.isEqual` in PhantomJS doesn't go to the `equalByTag` method when comparing two sets.

